<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id521f310e-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s2"><num value="2">§ 2.</num><heading> Terms of court</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Supreme Court shall hold at the seat of government a term of court commencing on the first Monday in October of each year and may hold such adjourned or special terms as may be necessary.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id521f310f-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/869">62 Stat. 869</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id521f3110-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id521f3111-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 338 (<ref href="/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s230">Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 230</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/36/1156">36 Stat. 1156</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1916-09-06/ch448/s1">Sept. 6, 1916, ch. 448, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/39/726">39 Stat. 726</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Minor changes in phraseology were made.</p>
</note>
